The paper deals with algorithms for learning and approximation of Boolean functions, which are central topics in computer science. The Chow Parameters Problem is a fundamental problem in learning theory, and the paper presents a new algorithm for solving it. The paper also provides improved algorithms for related problems in learning theory. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves Fourier analysis, which is a common tool in algorithms and data structures, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also deals with information theory and approximation, which are relevant to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), respectively.
